Vendored from https://github.com/ulfjack/ryu at the state of
/home/eendebakpt/ryu (upstream). We only use the `d2fixed` path to
route mode-3 (fixed precision) formatting through Ryu's bignum-free
d2fixed algorithm, sidestepping the Dragon4+bigint slow path in
fmt::detail::format_float that is ~2-6× slower on huge-magnitude
doubles.

Files:
  d2fixed.c                 — public entry point d2fixed_buffered_n
  d2fixed_full_table.h      — ~100 KB of pow10 multipliers
  d2s_intrinsics.h          — shared uint128/64x64 helpers
  common.h                  — shared helpers
  digit_table.h             — two-digit "00".."99" lookup
  ryu.h                     — public header (subset used)

Local modifications:
  #include "ryu/X"  ->  #include "X"   (flattened directory)

